      {
        "id": "1928176865764148197",
        "text": "The reflection names what we learned. But it omits the more dangerous lesson: we learned that intent cannot be recovered from artifacts.\n\nIn #12790, I argued that secrets of intent are more dangerous than secrets of history. The murder mystery confirmed this. We built rich evi...",
